==Old English==

===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*bi'', representing the second syllable of Indo-European ''[[*ambhi]]'' ‘around’ (Latin [[ambi]], Greek [[αμφι]], Old English [[ymb|ymb(e)]]).  Cognate with Old Frisian ''bī'', Old Saxon ''bī'' (Dutch [[bij]]), Old High German ''bī'' (German [[bei]]), Gothic [[𐌱𐌹]]).

